title: For Sale:  Canik TP 9
postcontent:
I have for sale a canik tp 9 with just a hundred rounds fired .The TP9 is a polymer-framed 9mm pistol with a 17+1 capacity.  This is a full-size gun with a 4-inch barrel. The action type of the TP9 is a bit unusual. It is a striker-fired gun, but it works a bit like a DA/SA pistol with an exposed hammer. When you first load the pistol and drop the slide, you have the option of leaving it as is. The trigger will stay all the way forward if you don’t touch it, but a light tug on it will reveal no pull weight for the first two-thirds of its travel length, then it will click into place. Pull the trigger then and the result will be a crisp 5-pound trigger pull. Or, you can hit the decocker at the top rear of the slide. When decocked, the trigger stays forward and you will get a long, traditional DA pull of about 10 pounds.

The rear of the striker is painted red, and if you can see it through the hole in the back of the slide, you’ll know it is cocked. The pistol has no external safety.

The polymer frame of the TP9 accommodates interchangeable backstraps, and two sizes–small and large–were provided with the pistol. I have medium-small hands, and the large backstrap put too much bulk on the pistol for my taste, but those of you with larger hands will probably like it a lot.

1913 Erfurt Luger 9mm 
The upper and lower are missed matched. 
The upper is one serial number and the lower is a separate serial; however i do have one magazine that matches the lower serial numbers.
there is the original holster Dated 1916 with the Makers name Joseph Moll of hoch.
Two clips
Take down tool.
The Luger was brought back from WW1 where my grand father served in the US Army in France (have service medal for proof if needed). He died in the late 50's and it has not been fired since then until last weekend. Its been gone through and safe to fire. clean crisp, strong spring! Works like only a Luger can and just has an awesome motion to it with low recoil. I am not a gun collector and i got this from my father because i have coyotes where i live and wanted a safety device. Its a rare piece and i am sure a collector would enjoy it more as i just want simple safe hand gun for what i need, just seems wrong to ride around with this on my quad. 
I have more pics e-mail for them.
Might sell holster, clips and cleaning kit separate for the right price. The gun works great and is metal, i just have a hard time taking the almost 100 year old holster out on the farm.
